    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Threats From Iran, and Against Iran</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James Day letter says it is naive to think that Bush administration is trying to bluff Iran into line with leaked threats about bombing its nuclear facilities (April 11 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's naïve to think that the administration is just trying to bluff Iran into line with leaked threats about bombing its nuclear facilities.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's naïve to think that the administration is just trying to bluff Iran into line with leaked threats about bombing its nuclear facilities.</p>
        <p>It's more likely that the leaks come from people who know the administration is seriously considering a bombing campaign and want to prevent it.</p>
        <p>James Day  Berkeley, Calif., April 11, 2006</p>
      </block>
